<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-1744] code treats domain names or hostnames case sensitive. This will cause verification to fail because FQDN are case insensitive.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-1744</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;in class DefaultHostnameVerifier in the method  static boolean matchDomainRoot(final String host, final String domainRoot); and maybe else where the code treats domain names or hostnames case sensitive. This will cause verification to fail because FQDN are case insensitive.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;host.endsWith(domainRoot)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
